#Text=Shark Bay
#Text=Shark Bay is a World Heritage Site in Gascoyne , Western Australia .
#Text=It is famous for its amazing sites , and for its dolphins .
#Text=It is 830 km north of Perth .
#Text=Understand
#Text=Despite its adjacent ocean and bays , the world heritage shark bay area has a very dry climate , and very arid landscape .

#Text=That said , there are seasonal rains from the north , and weather from the south does intrude , but generally it has a sense of the rest of the coast towards the north west , dry , vast and endless .
#Text=History

#Text=The European history of the area goes back to when Dirk Hartog , the Dutch explorer landed at Shark Bay in 1616 , over 150 years before Captain Cook made his first landing at Kurnell in 1770 leading to the establishment of the British colony at Sydney 18 years later .
#Text=The Dutch were not attracted to the area , as it contained none of the spices or other valuables they were looking to trade or acquire .
#Text=Their further visits were largely the result of being blown off course on route to the Dutch East Indies ( modern day Indonesia ) .
#Text=Francois Peron National Park is named after a French naturalist who visited Shark Bay in 1801 and 1803 .
#Text=For many years it was a sheep station .
#Text=The government bought it in 1990 .
#Text=The old homestead is now a museum .
#Text=Landscape
#Text=Shark Bay region is a large set of islands and bodies of water .
#Text=There are beautiful beaches , including Shell Beach , made entirely of shells .
#Text=Flora and fauna
#Text=A large section of Shark Bay has been cleared of non-native wildlife and fenced off at the narrowest point to provide a conservation reserve for rare Australian wildlife .
#Text=The project is called Project Eden .
#Text=Many native animals have been released including the woylie , mallee fowl , southern brown bandicoot and bilby .
#Text=The Hamelin Pool Marine Nature Reserve is home to the stromatolites , a rare and ancient form of life .
#Text=By plane
#Text=Shark Bay Airport ( MJK ) is around 8 km from Denham , and around 16 km from Monkey Mia on the Monkey Mia Road .
#Text=The airport has a sealed landing strip , but no terminal facilities of any substance .
#Text=Skywest services the airport from Perth four times a week , and from Exmouth weekly .
#Text=Carnarvon is 350 km from Denham/Monkey Mia , and has daily flights from Perth .
#Text=By car
#Text=Shark Bay is around 1000 km drive north from Perth .
#Text=It is around 5000km drive from Sydney , and about as far away from Sydney as you can get on the Australian mainland .
#Text=Shark Bay Car Hire is a local operator .
#Text=None of the majors operate in the area .
#Text=Fees and permits
#Text=Shark Bay Marine Park and Hamelin Pool Marine Nature Reserve is free .
#Text=Francois Peron National Park is : $ 10 per car , $ 5 per motorbike , free for holders of WA National Park pass .
#Text=Holiday and annual passes are also available at Department of Environment and Conservation offices
#Text=Monkey Mia Reserve is : adult $ 6 , child $ 2 , family $ 12 .
#Text=Holiday permit ( valid for 4 weeks ) is : adult $ 9 , child $ 4 , family $ 22 .
#Text=Get around
#Text=Access to Shark Bay region and its features is via the towns of Monkey Mia and Denham .
#Text=These two locations are a small entry point to the larger area .
#Text=Named features of the region include : Francois Peron National Park , Dirk Hartog Island , Shell Beach , Shark Bay Marine Park , Hamelin Pool Marine Nature Reserve .
#Text=It was given World Heritage status in 1991 .
#Text=Monkey Mia is pronounced Monkey-My-Ah , not Monkey Mee-Ah .
#Text=The Shark Bay World Heritage Discover Centre is in Denham .
#Text=See
#Text=Monkey Mia Dolphins .
#Text=The wild dolphins come close to shore at the bay in the mornings .
#Text=It is possible to feed them .
#Text=This is in a supervised resort setting , so if you want to get close to the dolphins arrive as early as possible
#Text=Hamelin Pool .
#Text=Home of the oldest living organisms in the world .
#Text=Shell Beach .
#Text=A long beach , comprised of small shells , metres deep .
#Text=Eagle Bluff .
#Text=Francois Peron National Park .
#Text=Dirk Hartog Island .
#Text=Accessible by plane from Shark Bay airport by charter flight , or by 4wd and barge .
#Text=Barge crossing must be prearranged .
#Text=There is accommodation on the island .
#Text=Point Quobba .
#Text=Blowholes .
#Text=Steep Point .
#Text=The most westerly point on the Australian mainland .
#Text=salt mountain .
#Text=The salt mountain at the Useless Loop salt mines can be seen from Denham beach .
#Text=Do
#Text=Fishing .
#Text=Recreational fishing is allowed in Shark Bay , but there are special rules as it is a National Park .
#Text=Several charter boat providers operate from Denham .
#Text=Go next
#Text=Carnarvon and onto Exmouth heading north .
#Text=Kalbarri and Kalbarri National Park are to the south .
